Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a new data-driven information hiding scheme and introduces a new criteria for evaluation of the security of the generative steganography. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The proposed method uses semantic image inpainting for generative steganography, which is a computer vision task. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with information hiding in multimedia (images) using generative models. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed method uses a powerful generator for stego image generation, which is a machine learning model. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed method uses a generative model for stego image generation, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence.
